[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering serialization solutions**\n\nI’m thinking about implementing a Serializable surrogate. It looks like I’ll need to cast to BigInteger when using readObject, so that’s essential. I wonder if a custom ObjectOutputStream could write the BCDSAPublicKey data. It doesn't seem easy, but using `Externalizable` might make it possible. However, for `writeObject`, I’ll still need an instance to cover it properly. This might require a bit of extra planning!\n\n**Considering test class visibility**\n\nI’m thinking about whether a class could be package-private. It seems like the rules say that top-level test classes should be public, but helper classes don't have to be. I wonder if all top-level test classes need to comply with that rule. Do we need an extra file, or can a nested class work with a `$` in the filter? It might be better to avoid configuration altogether. Hm, let's see.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_00a49b4536a2451f0169fbd1fc8994819e9b66da33e6c9b7aa\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-9IY_Ko4hRSxOdJ50CEDQDqcP_tDRI4ho8uhzvqsJCtRKFqiYhMlCTp-TBWqL3bcM5FKlsA4vsrAYvdii8V9c9ykOYMmmBvVbSBQOM0By8OepBebLCnacBQZhdl-WA4V2kfsw6aZyNuD77onvRRTzKLneqkM69hdYV6Ipym6MdKkEH_FUqG5Av3yZJnqL7YDOMNiEvCp_mNSco1WAMNriUpdBXn1dwZ0VqVIyYGBTJkp-7oBVcveDo9RFH1DAzGhm2Hi_-sBjAcllCoiWyWtyvDrLf2fVem4QBf45xJdZdYuWpnfRQI_3JqMdDKfujD9qyuB49bAEmuX3bTgtU1ortYWQLDyYSWMOH5nwci03VHg2x-kqLP0_tGbFCoQF3FD0NS7xRuR4ukOeWw6xZEWrGHN0tQ_adsLPKjdh0t5y3wKypHz_f-yyzxJDc1KAXFxMsz5NRTmjiz9TrBXvxqovxRQ2OyIGbESpO7cfZ4lpvFPt_hBeXcUnVlqMcHKXSdonk7TFmAY_3U3YVrrp4IysfFkVJM574EDRgzYZufVZgNArUyw52mMl9QapdYVGYf3fPXlSS4KphcZ2gYHbJ_h-nQIvI9rCKTQFl3m3WeNsKCKDZEFSCUXGght1eNizUZ7Tc205P14UOIPCQ1-xz206lfoybXicFUXJaiYBhAwHQJcnQ2kLidi6LfR86iP1C0e4N4NRd6hXKQCuqTsL5c8f3QfnzcjqS5_f1hy_7gB1tLxLBZYxuRBEhhdV3TkckfhqPaFldrtcfd2tDuiE96pSU7mwTKGXj6yvLZ34lVKg0d48JlUF0-ldLfWyKEi9d7EAjGS27RspKzrUdKbT96